  "title": "Sales Engineer[East/B2B/Prefer with semiconductor experience but not necessary]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor sales performance, track targets, and prepare revenue forecasts.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and issue sales quotations.</li>\n  <li>Identify, pursue, and develop new business opportunities to expand the customer base.</li>\n  <li>Engage with customers to understand their needs, provide technical support, and address issues effectively.</li>\n  <li>Stay informed on industry trends, market conditions, and competitor activities.</li>\n  <li>Conduct market research and analysis to identify new opportunities and potential risks.</li>\n  <li>Provide recommendations to optimize sales processes, improve efficiency, and drive revenue growth.</li>\n  <li>Build and maintain strong relationships with key customers, partners, and distributors.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and present internal and external sales reports.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering or a related discipline.</li>\n  <li>1–2 years of experience in sales or business development.</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in the semiconductor industry will be an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills to collaborate with internal teams and external customers.</li>\n  <li>Proven ability to develop sales plans and implement effective strategies.</li>\n  <li>Track record of building and maintaining long-term customer and partner relationships.</li>\n  <li>Customer-focused mindset with the ability to identify needs and provide tailored solutions.</li>\n</ul>",
